ROMAN Abramovich’s daughter Sofia has shared an anti-Vladimir Putin message on Instagram following the Russian invasion of Ukraine. The sporting world has widely united in condemnation of the attack, which has prompted Uefa and Formula One, among others, to abandon major upcoming events in Russia.   Firmino out Carabao Cup final     Tyson Fury returns to Wembley for fight with Whyte     Makinde appoints Sole Administrator for 3SC   On Friday, Sofia Abramovich posted a graphic on her Instagram Stories which criticised Russian president Putin. It featured the word “Russia” crossed out and above it, it read “Putin wants a war with Ukraine”.